cjnIpxSapEnabled.description: Enable / Disable IPX SAP on this system.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterEntry.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterEntry
cjnIpxSapNameFilterEntry.description: A Cajun IPX SAP name filter instance.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterPrec.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterPrec
cjnIpxSapNameFilterPrec.description: The precedence of this SAP name filter. The precedence is relative to other SAP name filters on the same interface.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterRowStatus.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterRowStatus
cjnIpxSapNameFilterRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterName.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterName
cjnIpxSapNameFilterName.description: The service name which this filter matches. A single asterisk as the last character matches all service names which match all characters up to the asterisk.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterType.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterType
cjnIpxSapNameFilterType.description: The service type which this filter matches. A value of ffff matches all service types.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterDirection.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterDirection
cjnIpxSapNameFilterDirection.description: The direction of IPX SAP packets to which this filter applies. Inbound applies the filter only to SAP packets received on the interface. Outbound applies the filter only to SAP packets sent on the interface. Both applies the filter to SAP packets sent and received on the interface.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterAction.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterAction
cjnIpxSapNameFilterAction.description: The action to take if this filter matches an IPX SAP entry. Filter causes the SAP entry to be ignored in received SAP packets or suppressed in sent SAP packets. Allow causes the SAP entry to be accepted in received SAP packets or advertised in sent SAP packets.

cjnIpxSapNameFilterHops.name: cjnIpxSapNameFilterHops
cjnIpxSapNameFilterHops.description: Used to override the hops to reach the service specified in the SAP entry.

cjnIpxSapNetFilterEntry.description: A Cajun IPX SAP network filter instance.

cjnIpxSapNetFilterPrec.name: cjnIpxSapNetFilterPrec

cjnIpxSapNetFilterRowStatus.name: cjnIpxSapNetFilterRowStatus
cjnIpxSapNetFilterRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

cjnIpxSapNetFilterNet.name: cjnIpxSapNetFilterNet
cjnIpxSapNetFilterNet.description: The IPX network number of the service which this filter matches. A value of ffffffff matches all service network numbers.

cjnIpxSapNetFilterType.name: cjnIpxSapNetFilterType
cjnIpxSapNetFilterType.description: The service type which this filter matches. A value of ffff matches all service types.

cjnIpxSapNetFilterDirection.name: cjnIpxSapNetFilterDirection
cjnIpxSapNetFilterDirection.description: The direction of IPX SAP packets to which this filter applies. Inbound applies the filter only to SAP packets received on the interface. Outbound applies the filter only to SAP packets sent on the interface. Both applies the filter to SAP packets sent and received on the interface.

cjnIpxSapNetFilterAction.name: cjnIpxSapNetFilterAction
cjnIpxSapNetFilterAction.description: The action to take if this filter matches an IPX SAP entry. Filter causes the SAP entry to be ignored in received SAP packets or suppressed in sent SAP packets. Allow causes the SAP entry to be accepted in received SAP packets or advertised in sent SAP packets.

cjnIpxSapNetFilterHops.name: cjnIpxSapNetFilterHops
cjnIpxSapNetFilterHops.description: Used to override the hops to reach the service specified in the SAP entry.

cjnIpxSapIfTable.description: A list of Cajun IPX SAP interface entries.

cjnIpxSapIfEntry.name: cjnIpxSapIfEntry
cjnIpxSapIfEntry.description: A Cajun IPX SAP interface instance.

cjnIpxSapIfRowStatus.name: cjnIpxSapIfRowStatus
cjnIpxSapIfRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or old entries deleted from this table.

cjnIpxSapIfInterpacketGap.name: cjnIpxSapIfInterpacketGap
cjnIpxSapIfInterpacketGap.description: If set to enable(1), IPX SAP packets from periodic advertisements are sent with an interpacket gap of 55 milliseconds. If set to disable(2), no interpacket gap is used.

cjnIpxSapIfUseMaximumPacketSize.name: cjnIpxSapIfUseMaximumPacketSize
cjnIpxSapIfUseMaximumPacketSize.description: If set to enable(1), IPX SAP packets will contain as many entries as will fit in the maximum packet size allowable on the interface given the configured encapsulation type. If set to disable(2), IPX SAP packets will contain at most 7 entries.

cjnIpxSapIfUpdateInterval.name: cjnIpxSapIfUpdateInterval
cjnIpxSapIfUpdateInterval.description: The SAP periodic update interval, in seconds.

cjnIpxSapIfAgeMultiplier.name: cjnIpxSapIfAgeMultiplier
cjnIpxSapIfAgeMultiplier.description: The holding multiplier for information received in SAP updates. SAP information will be kept for the number of seconds indicated by the cjnIpxSapIfUpdateInterval multiplied by the cjnIpxSapIfAgeMultiplier.

cjnIpxSapIfTriggeredUpdates.name: cjnIpxSapIfTriggeredUpdates
cjnIpxSapIfTriggeredUpdates.description: Specified whether or not SAP updates are immediately sent on the interface in response to changes in the routing table.

cjnIpxSapIfGetNearestServerReply.name: cjnIpxSapIfGetNearestServerReply
cjnIpxSapIfGetNearestServerReply.description: Specifies whether or not SAP Get Nearest Server replies are sent on the interface.

cjnIpxSapIfGetNearestServerReplyDelay.name: cjnIpxSapIfGetNearestServerReplyDelay
cjnIpxSapIfGetNearestServerReplyDelay.description: Specifies the delay in milliseconds to wait before sending a SAP Get Nearest Server reply after receiving a SAP Get Nearest Server request.

cjnIpxSapIfMode.name: cjnIpxSapIfMode
cjnIpxSapIfMode.description: The handling of SAP packets on the interface. If set to talk(1), SAP packets may be sent on the interface but not received. If set to listen(2), SAP packets may be received but not sent. If set to both(3), SAP packets may be sent and received.

cjnIpxSapIfStatTable.name: cjnIpxSapIfStatTable
cjnIpxSapIfStatTable.description: A list of Cajun IPX SAP interface statistics entries.

cjnIpxSapIfStatUpdatesReceived.description: The number of SAP updates received on the interface.

cjnIpxSapIfStatRequestsReceived.description: The number of SAP requests received on the interface.

cjnIpxSapIfStatGNSRequestsReceived.description: The number of SAP Get Nearest Server requests received on the interface.

cjnIpxSapIfStatBadPacketsReceived.description: The number of incorrectly formatted SAP packets received on the interface.

cjnIpxSapIfStatsReset.description: When set to the value enable (1) all IPX SAP statistics for this interface are reset to zero after which the value of this MIB object returns to disable(2).
